    <!-- What is Energy Systems Engineering Section -->
    <section class="section" id="about">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">What is Energy Systems Engineering?</h2>
            <div class="content-wrapper">
                <div class="text-content">
                    <p>Energy Systems Engineering is an interdisciplinary field that combines principles from mechanical engineering, electrical engineering, chemical engineering, and environmental science to design, optimize, and manage energy systems across various scales.</p>
                    <p>This specialized discipline focuses on the efficient generation, conversion, transmission, distribution, and utilization of energy from various sources, with an emphasis on sustainability, reliability, and economic viability.</p>
                    <p>Energy Systems Engineers develop solutions for complex energy challenges, including renewable energy integration, smart grid technologies, energy storage systems, and energy efficiency improvements in buildings, transportation, and industrial processes.</p>
                </div>
